snippet.textDisplay: Haha I was SEVERELY addicted to benzodiazepines. Research chemical benzos too. My drugs of choice were Clonozolam and Flubromazolam, the latter being active at ONLY 100 micrograms. By the end of my addiction (a short 4-6 months I can’t remember any of it) I was doing thumbprints of the flubromazolam. I quit cold turkey and refused medical assistance. I endured a total of 2 seizures I know of and potentially a third one that I am unsure of. They are fucking SCARY. GABA withdrawals are WORSE THAN HEROIN WITHDRAWAL! You’re in a constant state of panic and delirium 24 hours a day. If anyone had any questions leave a comment below I would love to answer anything concerning my experience.
